=== M10 complete — blacklight v0.1.0 ship-ready ===

- M9.5 P9 | Apr 25 2026 — sentinel fixup (chown-time TOCTOU close + test rename):
[Fix] src/bl.d/83-clean.sh — bl_clean_unquarantine now applies chown /
      chmod / touch to the *staged inode* before the final `mv -T`,
      not after. Closes the residual chown-time TOCTOU window: GNU
      chown/chmod follow symlinks by default, so post-rename
      ownership/mode application could be redirected onto an
      attacker-raced symlink target between rename(2) and chown.
      Rename-after-prep is the standard pattern (sentinel SHOULD-FIX-1).
      Post-rename `[[ -L ]]` retained as warning — restored inode is
      already correctly attributed; the warn surfaces parent-dir
      hostile activity for operator audit.
[Fix] tests/06-defend.bats — clamav rc=2 test renamed from "returns
      BL_EX_PREFLIGHT_FAIL (65)" to "collapses to TIER_GATE_DENIED at
      apply"; the gate-internal rc=65 is correctly intercepted by the
      apply layer and surfaced as 68 to the operator (sentinel INFO-1).
      Test assertion was already correct; only the name was misleading.
[Change] bl — regenerated.

