- M9.5 P4 | Apr 25 2026 — apache observe hot-path rewrite (M6/M7/M8/m17):
[Fix] src/bl.d/40-observe-helpers.sh — _bl_obs_emit_jsonl collapses
      `jq -n | _bl_obs_scrub` two-process pipeline into a single jq
      invocation with inline `walk(...)` scrub. Halves jq fork count
      per record across all observe handlers (audit M6).
[Change] src/bl.d/40-observe-helpers.sh — _bl_obs_scrub helper removed
      (only caller was emit_jsonl; scrub patterns inlined). Anti-slop
      orphan-helper cleanup.
[Fix] src/bl.d/41-observe-collectors.sh — bl_observe_log_apache awk now
      applies --window via mktime(); records outside [ws, we] are
      dropped before emit. Prior version computed ws/we but never
      filtered, emitting every record regardless of operator's window
      (audit M8). On gawk-less awks (BSD, mawk) mktime returns -1 and
      the filter falls through (safe behavior; matches pre-fix).
[Fix] src/bl.d/41-observe-collectors.sh — bl_observe_log_apache
      summary counters (total_records, post_to_php_count,
      status_histogram) now accumulated awk-side and emitted to
      summary file at END. Prior bash post-emit jq queried
      `.record.is_post_to_php` against unwrapped awk output, returning
      null every time and silently always-zero histograms (audit M7
      correctness bug).
[Change] src/bl.d/41-observe-collectors.sh — useless cat-subshell
      passthrough (`done < <(while ... done < tmpfile)`) collapsed to
      direct file read (audit m17).
[New] tests/04-observe.bats — 2 apache regression cases:
      summary-histogram counters are non-zero on apsb25-94 fixture;
      narrow --window drops records relative to broad --window.
