- v2 pivot | Apr 24 2026 — skills-first clean-room rewrite:

Rationale. v1 (Apr 21-23) wrapped Opus 4.7 in a Python/Flask curator
+ SQLite evidence.db + fs/log/timeline hunters + bl-agent fleet.
Three days in, the shape was upside-down: hunters duplicated
reasoning a Managed Agent with authored skills does natively, "live
IR" framing didn't fit the post-incident operator reality (known-bad
hosts, signature already fired), and the Python surface was eating
attention owed to case layout and skills. v2 inverts — bash `bl`
CLI, Managed Agents curator holding case state across sim-days,
9-file per-case layout, safety-tier gates, ≥20-file public-source
skills bundle.

Discarded. Flask curator; SQLite evidence.db; fs/log/timeline
hunters; orchestrator + case_engine + revise/apply_revision; bl-agent
pull/apply/report + bl-ctl; synthesizer + apachectl wrapper;
demo/time_compression sim runner; compose 7-host fleet; audit
pipeline (P0-P2, M-1..M-4); 6 v1 curator prompts.

Rebuilt forward. Managed Agents curator (v2 adds session wiring,
Files-API brief rendering, persisted case state). APSB25-94 PolyShell
knowledge, reconstructed into v2 fixtures from the public Adobe
advisory — no v1 artifact copied. Skills discipline (20-file floor,
public-source); 19/~28 v1 skills reconciled, rest rewritten or
retired. batsman submodule for tests (v1 used pytest).

Archive. v1 preserved at tag `legacy-pre-pivot` (`git checkout
legacy-pre-pivot`); legacy/ dropped from main after tag cut.
Clean-room on runtime per project CLAUDE.md §License. Shared rfxn
infra (`batsman`, `pkg_lib`) is open-source GPL v2 on public GitHub —
treated as external OSS dependencies, permitted under the hackathon
rules' OSS clause — scoped to test scaffolding and package manifests;
`bl` never sources either at runtime.
